<!-- Slide 2: Introduction -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">What is the Balanced Scorecard?</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div>
                <p>The Balanced Scorecard (BSC) is a strategic management performance metric used to identify and improve various internal business functions and their resulting external outcomes.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Developed by <strong>Dr. Robert Kaplan</strong> and <strong>Dr. David Norton</strong> in the early 1990s, it revolutionized how companies measure success by moving beyond financial metrics alone.</p>
                <ul style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <li>Connects everyday work to strategy</li>
                    <li>Prioritizes projects and products</li>
                    <li>Measures and monitors progress</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Business executives analyzing strategic data">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 3: The 4 Perspectives Overview -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">The Four Perspectives</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="tiled-content">
            <div class="tile">
                <div class="icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i></div>
                <h3>Financial</h3>
                <p>To succeed financially, how should we appear to our shareholders?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
                <div class="icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-users"></i></div>
                <h3>Customer</h3>
                <p>To achieve our vision, how should we appear to our customers?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
                <div class="icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-gears"></i></div>
                <h3>Internal Process</h3>
                <p>To satisfy our shareholders and customers, at what processes must we excel?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
                <div class="icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-seedling"></i></div>
                <h3>Learning & Growth</h3>
                <p>To achieve our vision, how will we sustain our ability to change and improve?</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 4: Financial Perspective -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">1. Financial Perspective</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div>
                <h3>The Traditional View</h3>
                <p>This perspective focuses on financial performance and the use of financial resources. It asks whether the company's strategy, implementation, and execution are contributing to bottom-line improvement.</p>
                <br>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Revenue Growth:</strong> Expanding to new markets or products.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cost Reduction:</strong> Lowering unit costs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Asset Utilization:</strong> Efficient use of capital.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551288049-bebda4e38f71?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Chart showing upward financial growth">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 5: Customer Perspective -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">2. Customer Perspective</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521791136064-7986c2920216?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Handshake representing customer satisfaction">
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>The Customer's View</h3>
                <p>This perspective identifies the customer and market segments in which the business unit will compete. It aligns organizational measures with customer expectations.</p>
                <br>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Customer Satisfaction:</strong> Are clients happy?</li>
                    <li><strong>Retention:</strong> Do they come back?</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Share:</strong> Percentage of the market controlled.</li>
                    <li><strong>Brand Image:</strong> Perception in the market.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 6: Internal Process Perspective -->
<div class="slide-container bleed-image-layout">
    <div class="content-container">
        <h2 class="slide-title" style="border:none;">3. Internal Process Perspective</h2>
        <div class="content-area">
            <p>This perspective focuses on the internal processes that are critical to success. It answers the question: <strong>"To satisfy our shareholders and customers, at what business processes must we excel?"</strong></p>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Managers identify the critical processes at which they must excel to satisfy customer and shareholder objectives.</p>
            <ul style="margin-top: 20px; color: #cbd5e1; list-style: disc; padding-left: 20px;">
                <li>Quality optimization (Defect rates).</li>
                <li>Cycle time reduction.</li>
                <li>Innovation processes.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="image-container">
        <img class="bleed-image-side" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581091226825-a6a2a5aee158?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Technology and processes">
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 7: Learning & Growth Perspective -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">4. Learning & Growth Perspective</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div>
                <h3>The Foundation</h3>
                <p>Also known as "Organizational Capacity," this perspective identifies the intangible assets that are most important for strategy. It is the foundation upon which the other three perspectives are built.</p>
                <br>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Human Capital:</strong> Skills, talent, and knowledge.</li>
                    <li><strong>Information Capital:</strong> Databases, networks, and IT infrastructure.</li>
                    <li><strong>Organization Capital:</strong> Culture, leadership, and teamwork.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522071820081-009f0129c71c?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Team training and development workshop">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 8: Strategy Maps -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">Visualizing Strategy: The Strategy Map</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531403009284-440f080d1e12?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Diagram showing strategy map connections">
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Connecting the Dots</h3>
                <p>A Strategy Map is a visual representation of the cause-and-effect relationships among the objectives in the four perspectives.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 20px;"><strong>The Logic Flow:</strong></p>
                <p>Improvements in <em>Learning & Growth</em> lead to better <em>Internal Processes</em>, which drive <em>Customer Satisfaction</em>, ultimately resulting in <em>Financial Success</em>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 9: Key Benefits -->
<div class="slide-container">
    <h2 class="slide-title">Key Benefits of the BSC</h2>
    <div class="content-area">
        <div class="bullet-list-container">
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Alignment:</strong> Aligns business activities to the vision and strategy of the organization.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-solid fa-comments"></i> <strong>Communication:</strong> Improves internal and external communications, and monitors organization performance against strategic goals.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-solid fa-bullseye"></i> <strong>Focus:</strong> Helps prioritize projects and initiatives that truly drive the strategy forward.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-pie"></i> <strong>Holistic View:</strong> Provides managers with a comprehensive picture of business operations, not just financials.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

